The federal government and the Japanesetrading company, C. Itoh and Co Ltd, have signed a letter ofunderstanding to try and boost trade ties between the twocountries, the Industry department said.    The two parties have agreed to encourage direct Japaneseinvestment in Canada, bilateral trade, and more joint venturesand licensing accords between Canadian and Japanese companies.    C. Itoh has just begun a trade mission in Canada toinvestigate trading opportunities in the aerospace, autopartselectronics and other sectors and will visit some 30 leadingcompanies across Canada.  Reuter&#3;